value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Sclerophthora macrospora. It is a causal agent for rice Downy Mildew disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice ragged stunt virus. It is a causal agent for rice ragged stunt disease.
The treatment involving day light as the light of the sun or the artificial light in a growth chamber.

definition.value: A type of light used in a commercial light box to simulate natural daylight. For experiments carried out in growth chambers, the daylight is a light source providing a color temperature of 6500+/-200 K at an illumination of 90 to 120 ft/candles. This source is typically provided by fluorescent,  tungsten or halogen lamps.

value.value: The treatment involving an exposure to varying degree of humidity, which may depend on regional environment.
A physical plant exposure (PECO:0007316) involving an exposure of varying amounts of water and watering frequencies, which may depend on regional environment.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to long day light duration followed by a short night cycle.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to short day light duration followed by a long night cycle.
The treatment using infra red (IR) light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving IR light in the wavelength range of 700nm-1mm.
The treatment using far red light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving red color light in the wavelength range of 800-700 nM.
An auxin exposure (PECO:0007074) involving use of 1-naphthaleneacetic acid growth hormone and herbicide.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice grassy stunt 2 virus. It is a causal agent for rice grassy stunt disease.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Gaeumannomyces graminis. It is a causal agent for rice Crown Sheath Rot Disease also called as Arkansas Foot Rot Disease, Black Sheath Rot Disease and Brown Sheath Rot Disease.
The treatment using red light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving red color light in the wavelength range of 780-622 nM.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice grassy stunt 1 virus. It is a causal agent for rice grassy stunt disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Phomopsis oryzae-sativae.

definition.value: It is a causal agent for rice Collar Rot Disease.

value.value: A biotic plant exposure (PECO:0007357) involving exposure of a plant to a virus or a combination of two or more viruses.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Cochliobolus miyabeanus. It is a causal agent for rice Brown Spot diseaseand/or Seedling Blight (Fungal) disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the mycoplasma pest.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogenic Alternaria sp.
The treatment using orange light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving orange color light in the wavelength range of 622-597 nM.
The treatment using yellow light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving yellow color light in the wavelength range of 597-577 nM.
The treatment using green light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving green color light in the wavelength range of 577-492 nM.
The treatment using blue light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving blue color light in the wavelength range of 492-455 nM.
The treatment using indigo light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving indigo color light in the wavelength range of 450-440 nM.
The treatment using violet light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light treatment involving violet color light in the wavelength range of 455-390 nM.
The treatment using visible light in the wavelength range of 380-780 nM.

definition.value: Visible light  is the portion of the electromagnetic spectrum that is visible to the human eye. The optical spectrum is a composite, or mixture, of the various colors.

value.value: The treatment using UV-B light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental light involving electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of 315-10nm.
A cadmium exposure (PECO:0001018) involving use of CdCl2 (CHEBI:35456).

definition.value: Can be used to assess plant response to cadmium, a heavy metal.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant or a plant part to the amount of light energy incident upon (or flowing through) unit area, perpendicular to the radiation source, in unit time.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to fluorine as supplement to study various types of responses.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Magnaporthe grisea. It is a causal agent for rice various forms of Blast diseases such as Collar Blast, Leaf Blast, Neck Blast, Panicle Blast and Nodal Blast disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Cochliobolus lunatus.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to chromium as supplement to study various types of responses.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Gibberella fujikuroi.

definition.value: It is a causal agent for rice Bakanae disease and also for a form of rice Seedling Blight (Fungal) Disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to iodine as supplement to study various types of responses.
A plant experimental condition (PECO:0007359) or set of conditions describing what kind of plant growth facility was used for the experiment.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to selenium as supplement to study various types of responses.
A biotic plant exposure (PECO:0007357) involving exposure of a plant to a fungus or a combination of fungi.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Pseudomonas fuscovaginae. It is a causal agent for rice Sheath Brown Rot disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to silicon as supplement to study various types of responses.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Pseudomonas plantarii. It is a causal agent for rice Seedling Blight (Bacterial) disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to elements that are required in tiny quantities for growth, as supplement to study various types of responses.
A plant nutrient exposure (PECO:0007241) involving the use of a plant macronutrient or combination of plant macronutrients.

definition.value: The macronutrients comprise the elements required by the plant in relatively large quantities for normal growth.

value.value: A plant chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving a plant nutrient or a combination of plant nutrients.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to micronutrient iron as supplement to study various types of responses.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Pseudomonas glumae. It is a causal agent for rice Grain Rot disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to micronutrient chlorine as supplement to study various types of responses.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Erwinia chrysanthemi. It is a causal agent for rice Foot Rot disease.
A biotic plant exposure (PECO:0007357) involving exposure of a plant to bacteria.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Erwinia herbicola. The susceptible plants suffer from Bacterial Palea Browning disease.
